---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="About — Arden de Raaij">
  <header class="page-header" data-rise data-rise-delay="0.05">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1 class="page-title">A bit of background</h1>
  </header>

  <section class="section about-prose" data-rise data-rise-delay="0.14">
    <p>
      I'm Arden, a senior front-end engineer from Amsterdam, living in Lisbon
      since 2017.
    </p>
    <p>
      I've been building for the web since 2008 — the first decade or so
      freelance and in Amsterdam agencies, everything from full-stack sites to
      front-end tooling.
    </p>
    <p>
      Since moving to Portugal I've worked across the range: agency work at <a
        href="https://www.eae.pt/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener">East Atlantic Engineering</a
      >, then product teams at <a
        href="https://www.mercedes-benz.io/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener">Mercedes-Benz.io</a
      >, <a href="https://www.plumguide.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
        >Plum Guide</a
      >, and now <a
        href="https://www.publicisgroupe.com/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener">the Publicis Groupe</a
      >. Consumer marketplaces, automotive platforms, media-planning tools,
      mostly React and TypeScript, usually the complex, data-heavy kind, and
      often the design-system layer underneath. At this point the work is as
      much architecture, setting the bar for front-end quality, and mentoring
      other developers as it is writing components myself. I came at this from
      the creative side rather than computer science, which is probably why I
      care as much about how a thing feels to use as how it's built underneath.
    </p>
    <p>
      Away from client work I'm a tinkerer. I run a homelab, self-host most of
      the tools I depend on, and build small things for myself like a
      self-hosted fitness-tracking stack, MCP tooling, and various automation
      scripts. I like owning my own data and understanding what I rely on.
    </p>
    <p>
      When I'm not at a keyboard I'm usually behind a camera, out running, on a
      snowboard, or somewhere out in the city. My photography lives over at <a
        href="https://instagram.com/ardennl"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener">Instagram</a
      >.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you're after the formal CV, that's on <a
        href="https://linkedin.com/in/ardenderaaij"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a
      >.
      {
        /* Restore when the blog is back: If you'd rather see how I think, the
      <a href="/writing">writing's</a> a better place to start. */
      }
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .about-prose {
    max-width: 64ch;
  }

  .about-prose p {
    margin: 0 0 22px;
    font-size: clamp(17px, 2.1vw, 19px);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--intro);
  }

  .about-prose p:last-child {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about-prose a {
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: none;
    box-shadow: inset 0 -1.5px 0 var(--blue);
  }
</style>
